      <h2>History</h2>
      <p>Bihar boasts a rich and ancient history, dating back 3,000 years. It was home to several powerful empires, including the Magadha Empire, the Mauryan Empire under Ashoka the Great, the Gupta Empire, and the Pala Empire.</p>
      <h3>Dynasties with Capitals in Bihar</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magadha_Empire">Magadha Empire</a> (Capital: Rajgir, later Pataliputra)
          <ul>
            <li>One of the most powerful empires in ancient India, ruled by dynasties like the Mauryas, Shishunagas, and Nandas.</li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mauryan_Empire">Mauryan Empire</a> (Pataliputra) - Ruled by Ashoka, who spread Buddhism
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gupta_Empire">Gupta Empire</a> (Pataliputra) - Known as India's Golden Age for its contributions to science, math, and literature
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pala_Empire">Pala Empire</a> (Patna, later Bengal) - Promoted Buddhism and established universities like Vikramashila
        </li>
      </ul>
